    <p>LON­DON • West Ham are los­ing £2 mil­lion</p>
    <p>(S$3.6 mil­lion) a match with spec­ta­tors barred from at­tend­ing games amid the Covid-19 pan­demic, the Premier League foot­ball club’s vice-chair­man Kar­ren Brady said.</p>
    <p>She called the lock­out since the restart in June “fa­tal for ev­ery­body”, re­veal­ing that other clubs “are los­ing as much as</p>
    <p>£10 mil­lion a match”.</p>


